        <mxCell id="500" parent="Z8O4pT-hFiafL0M5wHAX-504" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#888800;fillColor=#ffffee;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=7;fontColor=#333300;" value="&lt;b&gt;FASTENER / MATERIAL NOTES (v7)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Ledger: 1/2in hot-dip galv lag bolts or LedgerLOK, 16in o.c. staggered; Z-flashing above&lt;br/&gt;Lateral ties: min. 2x Simpson MTWDeck per IRC R507.9 / DCA-6&lt;br/&gt;Face-hung joists: Simpson LUS210Z hot-dip galv; LUS210-2Z for doubled rim&lt;br/&gt;Helical pier saddles: Pylex saddle plate, 1/2in hot-dip galv bolts to pier shaft top; 1/2in galv lag bolts up into girder&lt;br/&gt;Drop-board sub-fascia: 2x outboard of each exposed edge at joist elevation&lt;br/&gt;Framing: 2x10 PT UC4B ground-contact throughout. No posts, no sonotubes.&lt;br/&gt;Trex Universal Fascia: 0.75in, stainless trim screws to rim outer face&lt;br/&gt;Piers: Pylex 50 helical pier, 50in galvanized shaft, screwed to refusal through punched patio holes&lt;br/&gt;Hardware: hot-dip galvanized or stainless throughout (ACQ-compatible)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="180" width="480" x="-590" y="980" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
